{"image_id": "CINF_2011_page_65", "image_size": [1275, 1650], "ocr": [{"text": "Cincinnati Financial Corporation – 2011 10-K - 63", "bbox": [461.2, 1592.9, 840.9, 1615.2]}, {"text": "Commercial Property", "bbox": [150.0, 57.6, 380.3, 89.6]}, {"text": "Commercial property net written premiums and earned premiums for 2011 rose, largely due to improving", "bbox": [150.0, 594.1, 1117.4, 621.7]}, {"text": "pricing trends.", "bbox": [150.0, 618.1, 292.5, 645.8]}, {"text": "The 2011 total loss and loss expense ratio rose 16.3 percentage points primarily due to a 16.1 point", "bbox": [150.0, 648.1, 1072.5, 675.8]}, {"text": "increase in catastrophe losses. In addition, the ratio increased 5.2 percentage points from higher large", "bbox": [150.0, 672.1, 1095.4, 699.8]}, {"text": "losses related to fires, and it also rose from other weather-related losses that were not identified as part of", "bbox": [150.0, 696.2, 1129.6, 723.8]}, {"text": "designated catastrophe events for the property casualty industry, typically referred to as non-catastrophe", "bbox": [150.0, 720.2, 1119.2, 747.8]}, {"text": "weather losses. The effect of the $13 million ceded to reinstate coverage layers of our property catastrophe", "bbox": [150.0, 744.2, 1141.9, 771.8]}, {"text": "reinsurance treaty increased the 2011 ratio by 2.2 percentage points. The refined line of business allocation", "bbox": [150.0, 768.2, 1145.7, 795.8]}, {"text": "process for loss expenses reduced the 2011 total loss and loss expense ratio by 3.5 percentage points and", "bbox": [150.0, 791.9, 1140.9, 819.6]}, {"text": "also had the effect of decreasing the ratio for current accident year before catastrophe losses.", "bbox": [150.0, 815.9, 1024.2, 843.6]}, {"text": "The 2011 current accident year loss and loss expense ratio before catastrophe losses also rose, compared", "bbox": [150.0, 846.2, 1139.4, 873.8]}, {"text": "with accident year 2010, largely due to higher large losses from fires and increased losses from", "bbox": [150.0, 870.2, 1033.8, 897.8]}, {"text": "non-catastrophe weather. In 2011, we began full use of predictive modeling tools for property coverages in", "bbox": [150.0, 894.2, 1134.9, 921.8]}, {"text": "our commercial package accounts to improve our pricing precision. We also increased our loss control staff,", "bbox": [150.0, 918.0, 1148.2, 945.6]}, {"text": "including more specialization in the areas of conducting property inspections for both new and renewal", "bbox": [150.0, 942.0, 1097.9, 969.6]}, {"text": "business. We believe these initiatives will improve profitability over time.", "bbox": [150.0, 966.0, 823.9, 993.6]}, {"text": "Commercial Auto", "bbox": [150.0, 995.4, 339.0, 1027.4]}, {"text": "Net written premiums and earned premiums for commercial auto were up in 2011, partly from improving", "bbox": [150.0, 1528.1, 1109.6, 1555.7]}, {"text": "pricing trends. Commercial auto is one of the business lines that we renew and price annually, so market", "bbox": [150.0, 1552.1, 1119.0, 1579.8]}, {"text": "(Dollars in millions)", "bbox": [111.4, 94.5, 217.4, 111.5]}, {"text": "2011", "bbox": [637.3, 113.0, 669.8, 134.4]}, {"text": "2010", "bbox": [745.9, 113.6, 778.4, 134.8]}, {"text": "2009", "bbox": [854.5, 113.6, 887.0, 134.8]}, {"text": "Commercial property:", "bbox": [111.8, 133.6, 254.4, 154.7]}, {"text": "Net written premiums", "bbox": [111.8, 153.6, 264.7, 174.7]}, {"text": "$", "bbox": [603.5, 153.3, 611.5, 174.7]}, {"text": "512", "bbox": [659.6, 153.8, 684.0, 175.3]}, {"text": "$", "bbox": [712.1, 153.6, 720.1, 174.7]}, {"text": "497", "bbox": [768.2, 153.8, 792.6, 174.9]}, {"text": "$", "bbox": [820.7, 153.6, 828.7, 174.7]}, {"text": "485", "bbox": [876.8, 153.8, 901.2, 174.9]}, {"text": "3", "bbox": [988.3, 153.8, 996.4, 175.3]}, {"text": "2", "bbox": [1096.9, 153.8, 1105.0, 174.9]}, {"text": "Earned premiums", "bbox": [111.8, 173.5, 237.9, 194.6]}, {"text": "497", "bbox": [659.6, 173.8, 684.0, 195.2]}, {"text": "489", "bbox": [768.2, 173.7, 792.6, 19